verbose_text: Obstruction of lower limb arteries results in several clinical presentations ranging from no symptoms, through life-style limiting intermittent claudication (IC), in which patients ' walking ability is impaired, to critical limb ischemia (CLI), in which arterial flow is so severely reduced it causes chronic ischemic rest pain or even ischemic skin lesions, such as ulcers or gangrene.
